If there are three or more, I try to get the melees to move away from the mezzed mob to help isolate the unmezzed ones.  Or alternatively, root a mob right away and ask the melees to back off.  You may root the one they are on, but they'll soon enough switch targets to the one or ones that are beating on them.<br>
Of course, ideally you want to get them mezzed before they are both in front of your tank and all over each other.  Myself and the tank I play with most often have a system where if he is bringing in more than one mob the last one he calls will be the one he is on.   If the other is different named, choosing which one to mez is easy.  If you are in an open area you can agree with the puller that when multiples are coming in you can assist off the puller and mez the puller's current target before he reaches camp.<br>
